<$transclude $tiddler="$:/plugins/rimir/doc-template/templates/page">
<$fill $name="body">

!! Data flow

!!! Upload

# Browser: user drops file onto `<$file-dropzone>`
# Widget reads file via `wiki.readFiles()`, base64-encodes content
# Widget computes `targetPath` from file-paths filter (or `subfolder` attribute)
# Widget performs XHR &rarr; `POST /api/file-upload`
# Server validates MIME type, checks path traversal, writes file to `/files/<targetPath>`
# Server checks thumbnail settings &mdash; if enabled for this MIME type, runs ImageMagick via `runner-actions.json` to generate thumbnail in `_generated/`
# Server responds with `{canonicalUri, filename, generatedUri?}`
# Widget parses response, extracts `canonical-uri` and `generated-uri` as variables
# Widget executes `actions` callback &mdash; typically creates tiddler with `_canonical_uri` and `_thumbnail_uri`

!!! Rename

# Browser: user saves tiddler with a new title
# `th-saving-tiddler` hook detects title change + `_canonical_uri` on original tiddler
# Hook computes new file path from new title (preserving extension)
# Synchronous XHR &rarr; `POST /api/file-rename`
# Server renames file on disk, also renames `_generated/` files
# Hook updates `_canonical_uri` on the new tiddler

!!! Delete

# Browser: user deletes a tiddler with `_canonical_uri`
# `th-deleting-tiddler` hook shows confirmation dialog
# If confirmed, async XHR &rarr; `POST /api/file-delete`
# Server deletes file from disk, also deletes `_generated/` files
# Server cleans up empty parent directories

!! Components

|!Component |!Layer |!Role |
|`routes/upload.js` |Server |`POST /api/file-upload` &mdash; receive base64 file, validate, write to `/files/`, run thumbnail processor |
|`routes/rename.js` |Server |`POST /api/file-rename` &mdash; rename file on disk (incl. `_generated/`) |
|`routes/delete.js` |Server |`POST /api/file-delete` &mdash; delete file from disk (incl. `_generated/`) |
|`widgets/dropzone.js` |Browser |`<$file-dropzone>` &mdash; extends core dropzone, uploads via XHR, passes response variables to actions |
|`startup.js` |Browser |Registers `th-saving-tiddler` and `th-deleting-tiddler` hooks |
|`cascade-thumbnail.tid` |Browser |ViewTemplateBodyFilter &mdash; routes tiddlers with `_thumbnail_uri` to thumbnail body template |
|`body-thumbnail.tid` |Browser |Body template &mdash; shows thumbnail with click-to-expand, or full-size view |
|`toolbar-version-switch.tid` |Browser |ViewToolbar button &mdash; toggles between thumbnail and full-size view |
|`settings.tid` |Browser |Control Panel &rarr; Settings &rarr; File Upload |

!! Design decisions

* ''`th-saving-tiddler` not `th-renaming-tiddler`'' &mdash; the editor's save-with-new-title flow uses `addTiddler` + `deleteTiddler`, not `wiki.renameTiddler()`. The `th-saving-tiddler` hook is the only one that fires during editor renames.
* ''Synchronous XHR for rename'' &mdash; `th-saving-tiddler` must return the (possibly modified) tiddler synchronously. Modern browsers still support sync XHR on the main thread.
* ''`bodyFormat: "stream"` for upload'' &mdash; base64-encoded files can be large; streaming avoids TW's default body buffering limits.
* ''`_generated/` subfolder'' &mdash; post-upload processors write derived files (thumbnails) alongside the original. Rename and delete operations also handle `_generated/` files.
* ''Path traversal protection'' &mdash; all routes verify that resolved paths stay inside the `files/` directory using `path.relative()`.
* ''Direct XHR in dropzone widget'' &mdash; uses `$tw.utils.httpRequest` instead of `tm-http-request` so the widget can parse the server response and pass `canonical-uri` and `generated-uri` as action variables automatically.
* ''Settings-driven processors'' &mdash; thumbnail generation is controlled by config tiddlers (`thumb-images`, `thumb-pdfs`, `thumb-resolution`) read per request, not by the static `processors` tiddler.
* ''ViewTemplateBodyFilter cascade'' &mdash; thumbnail rendering hooks into TW's body cascade so it runs before the default template. Only activates when the tiddler has `_thumbnail_uri` and thumb-rendering is enabled.
* ''`$:/state/` for view toggle'' &mdash; thumbnail/full-size state uses `$:/state/file-upload/view-mode/<title>` (memory-only, not persisted).

<$transclude $tiddler="$:/plugins/rimir/doc-template/templates/callout" type="info">
<$fill $name="body">
The rename and delete routes operate on `/files/`, not `tiddlers/`. The filesystem-watcher plugin watches `tiddlers/` only, so there is no conflict or write-lock needed.
</$fill>
</$transclude>

!! Security model

* MIME type whitelist &mdash; only types listed in `$:/config/rimir/file-upload/media-types` are accepted (checked both client-side and server-side)
* Path traversal &mdash; `path.relative(basePath, resolved)` must not start with `..`
* CSRF &mdash; all POST routes require `X-Requested-With: TiddlyWiki` header
* File conflict &mdash; rename returns 409 if the target file already exists

</$fill>
</$transclude>